Always follow these rules for moblies-shop:

## Tech Stack

- Next.js 16 App Router (standalone Docker output)
- TypeScript (strict)
- PostgreSQL 16 + Prisma 6
- Auth.js Credentials + JWT session + bcryptjs (12 rounds)
- Tailwind CSS 4 + Radix UI (Shadcn-style in `components/ui/`)
- next-intl â€” Arabic (default, RTL) + English
- @react-pdf/renderer for A4 invoices
- Vitest for unit tests
- Zod validation in `lib/validations/`

## Architecture

- **Single shop per deployment** â€” NOT multi-tenant (unlike StoreLedger)
- Clean Architecture:
  - `lib/domain/` â€” errors, profit helpers, types
  - `lib/application/services/` â€” business logic (inventory, sale, purchase, report...)
  - `app/(dashboard)/*/actions.ts` â€” thin server actions
- No separate backend server â€” monolith Next.js
- Server actions for all mutations; minimal API routes (auth, search, invoice PDF)
- Action results: `{ success: true; id?: string } | { error: string }` via `lib/domain/action-result.ts`
- Server actions passed to client components must use `.bind(null, id)` â€” never inline arrow functions from RSC

## Auth & Roles

- Roles: `ADMIN` | `EMPLOYEE` on `User.role`
- JWT session includes: id, email, name, locale, role
- `requireUser()` â€” all authenticated routes
- `requireAdmin()` â€” `/users`, `/settings`, and their server actions
- Middleware blocks Employee from `/users` and `/settings`
- Bootstrap admin from `.env`: `ADMIN_EMAIL`, `ADMIN_PASSWORD` (min 6 chars), `ADMIN_NAME`, `ADMIN_LOCALE`

## Database (Prisma)

- Money: `Decimal @db.Decimal(12, 2)` â€” never Float
- IDs: `cuid()`
- Business dates: `@db.Date`; timestamps: `DateTime`
- Key models: User, ShopSettings, Warehouse, Category, Product, Sale, SaleItem, Purchase, PurchaseItem, SaleReturn, PurchaseReturn, Expense, Customer, Payment, StockTransfer, InvoiceSequence
- Use `prisma migrate deploy` in Docker via `scripts/docker-init.sh`
- Indexes on foreign keys and search fields (sku, barcode, name)

## Inventory & Stock Rules

- **All stock changes MUST use `prisma.$transaction`**
- Sale â†’ decrease `Product.quantity` (reject if insufficient)
- Purchase â†’ increase quantity + update costPrice
- SaleReturn â†’ increase quantity; reduce debt if ON_ACCOUNT sale
- PurchaseReturn â†’ decrease quantity (reject if insufficient)
- StockTransfer â†’ decrease source, increase/create in destination (match by SKU + warehouseId)
- SaleItem stores `costPriceSnapshot` at sale time for accurate profit reports
- Invoice numbers via `InvoiceSequence` + `ShopSettings.invoicePrefix`

## Profit Formulas

```
GrossProfit = Î£(saleItems: (unitPrice - costPriceSnapshot) Ă— qty) âˆ’ return margins
NetProfit   = GrossProfit âˆ’ Î£(expenses)
```

Implemented in `lib/domain/profit.ts` and `lib/application/services/report-service.ts`

## Financial / Business Rules

- Payment methods: CASH, CARD, ON_ACCOUNT
- ON_ACCOUNT sale requires customer â†’ increases `Customer.totalDebt`
- Customer payment decreases `totalDebt` (cannot exceed debt)
- Invoice PDF shows selling price only â€” NEVER cost price
- Expenses reduce net profit in reports

## Production & Docker

- Services: `postgres` â†’ `migrate` â†’ `app` (+ optional `seed` profile)
- `POSTGRES_DB=mobiles_shop`, `APP_PORT=3022` (default)
- `AUTH_URL` must match public URL (e.g. `http://localhost:3022`)
- `AUTH_SECRET` must be strong: `openssl rand -base64 32`
- On empty DB: `scripts/docker-init.sh` â†’ migrate + `prisma/bootstrap.ts`
- Bootstrap creates: admin user, shop settings, 2 warehouses, 5 default categories
- Demo data is opt-in: `docker compose --profile demo run --rm seed` or `npm run db:seed`
- **`public/` directory MUST exist** â€” Docker COPY fails without it
- Fresh start: `docker compose down -v` then `docker compose up -d --build`
- Do not commit `.env`; use `.env.example` as template

## UI Conventions

See **`.cursor/rules/ui-design-system.mdc`** for full design system (typography, colors, components, RTL).

- Route groups: `(auth)` for login, `(dashboard)` for app
- Sidebar grouped nav + mobile bottom nav (`components/layout/`)
- Nav config: `components/layout/nav-config.ts` â€” groups + adminOnly items
- Page headers: `PageHeader` component
- Data tables: wrap in `DataTableShell` from `components/ui/data-table-shell.tsx`
- Empty lists: use `EmptyState` from `components/ui/empty-state.tsx`
- Fonts: Inter + IBM Plex Sans Arabic (`app/layout.tsx`)
- Primary color: indigo SaaS palette (`app/globals.css`)

